WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:01.769
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Hey, you guys.

00:01.802 --> 00:02.770
Welcome back.

00:02.803 --> 00:03.804
When Jane was young,

00:03.836 --> 00:05.173
her grandmother taught her

00:05.206 --> 00:07.108
to protect her flower.

00:09.243 --> 00:10.644
And so, Jane waited.

00:10.678 --> 00:12.780
Which wasn't always easy.

00:12.813 --> 00:14.515
This was Jane's fiancé Michael.

00:14.548 --> 00:16.117
He's a detective.

00:16.149 --> 00:18.419
Their life was perfectly
 on track until...

00:18.452 --> 00:20.254
Oh, there you are,
Dr. Alver.

00:20.288 --> 00:22.223
You have an insemination
 in seven and a pap in eight.

00:22.256 --> 00:24.225
I got it.
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 She does not "got it."

00:24.258 --> 00:26.094
Are you ready
for your insemination?

00:26.127 --> 00:27.761
Hi, yes!

00:27.795 --> 00:29.830
I artificially inseminated
the wrong woman.

00:29.863 --> 00:31.832
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 And the father to be?

00:31.865 --> 00:35.069
Rafael Solano, the rich owner
 of the Marbella Hotel.

00:35.103 --> 00:37.605
See, Rafael had cancer

00:37.638 --> 00:40.308
so it was his very last sperm
 sample... or so he thought.

00:40.341 --> 00:41.809
But guess what happened?

00:41.842 --> 00:44.112
Jane and Rafael,
 they fell in love.

00:44.145 --> 00:46.147
So, Jane broke up with Michael.

00:46.180 --> 00:48.249
And Rafael broke up with Petra.

00:48.282 --> 00:51.219
Until Rafael started spiraling
 and broke up with Jane...

00:51.252 --> 00:53.754
which for the record,
 he really regrets.

00:53.787 --> 00:55.689
Also full of regrets?
 Petra.

00:55.723 --> 00:58.259
See, she owns
 part of Rafael's hotel,

00:58.292 --> 01:00.628
but she doesn't have
 the one thing she really wants.

01:00.661 --> 01:02.496
Rafael.
 So, when this happened...

01:02.530 --> 01:03.697
DIANE:
Your husband's sperm sample

01:03.731 --> 01:05.498
was split into two vials.

01:05.533 --> 01:07.535
One was misplaced.
We just found it.

01:07.568 --> 01:09.770
...she naturally took it
 herself.

01:09.803 --> 01:12.206
I know, straight out
 of a telenovela, right?

01:12.240 --> 01:14.342
Well, imagine this--

01:14.375 --> 01:16.677
Jane's father was
 international telenovela star

01:16.710 --> 01:18.746
Rogelio de la Vega.

01:18.779 --> 01:21.215
And he reconnected
 with her mother Xiomara.

01:21.249 --> 01:23.184
And remember Detective Michael?

01:23.217 --> 01:24.652
Well, he was on the hunt

01:24.685 --> 01:26.854
for Sin Rostro,
 a notorious crime boss

01:26.887 --> 01:29.757
who ran a plastic surgery ring,
 changing criminals' faces.

01:29.790 --> 01:33.194
And Sin Rostro turned out to be
 Rafael's stepmother Rose.

01:33.227 --> 01:35.829
And she disappeared and who
 knows what she looks like now?

01:35.863 --> 01:38.699
(whistling)
 I know, OMG, right?

01:38.732 --> 01:40.368
And speaking of OMG,

01:40.401 --> 01:41.735
Jane had her baby.

01:41.769 --> 01:43.171
A beautiful boy named Mateo,

01:43.204 --> 01:44.872
and then, this happened...

01:44.905 --> 01:46.774
Bye, Mateo.

01:48.442 --> 01:51.545
(whistling)

01:51.579 --> 01:53.814
Which, I'm afraid,
 is where we left off.

01:53.847 --> 01:55.749
(tires squealing)

02:09.663 --> 02:11.599
To give some context,

02:11.632 --> 02:13.267
last night's episode
 of The Miracles of Mariana

02:13.301 --> 02:16.304
ended with quite
 the frightening cliffhanger.

02:21.875 --> 02:23.777
JANE:
Yeah, but,

02:23.811 --> 02:26.314
I just don't know if I can
stomach all the ups and downs.

02:26.347 --> 02:27.548
Then don't watch.

02:27.581 --> 02:28.849
Of course I'm watching.

02:28.882 --> 02:31.485
(theme song playing)

02:31.519 --> 02:32.553
Did you make me...?

02:32.586 --> 02:33.821
Turn it up, Ma.

02:33.854 --> 02:35.389
(shushes)
(speaks Spanish)

03:06.487 --> 03:08.456
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Jane would think about

03:08.489 --> 03:10.791
that theme song briefly
 when she was told

03:10.824 --> 03:13.961
the worst news ever.

03:13.994 --> 03:16.264
But that hasn't happened yet.

03:16.297 --> 03:17.965
You see, we're only...

03:23.003 --> 03:24.972
JANE:
Definitely not that one.

03:25.005 --> 03:26.340
Wait, what's wrong
with this one?

03:26.374 --> 03:27.741
Well, he's got a hat on.

03:27.775 --> 03:28.876
We got to send one out
that shows his hair.

03:28.909 --> 03:29.877
He's known for his hair.

03:29.910 --> 03:30.944
He's known for his hair?

03:30.978 --> 03:32.413
Well, he will
be when we

03:32.446 --> 03:33.814
send out the birth
announcement.

03:33.847 --> 03:35.483
Hey, what are you two
doing over there?

03:35.516 --> 03:37.585
Nothing.
I agree.

03:37.618 --> 03:40.254
Just discussing their drunken
 wedding night in Vegas.

03:41.322 --> 03:42.923
Where's Mateo?
Matelio.

03:42.956 --> 03:45.426
How long's
the hearing test take anyway?

03:45.459 --> 03:46.994
He's only been gone
nine minutes.

03:47.027 --> 03:48.296
You timed it?

03:48.329 --> 03:49.630
We're on a nursing
schedule.

03:49.663 --> 03:50.764
You have to keep track.

03:50.798 --> 03:52.500
When he eats,
which boob,

03:52.533 --> 03:53.801
how long?

03:53.834 --> 03:54.802
Mom, it's helpful.

03:54.835 --> 03:56.270
Hey, there.
Hi.

03:56.304 --> 03:58.005
I'm here to take Mateo
for his hearing test.

03:58.038 --> 03:59.307
Oh, another nurse took him.

03:59.340 --> 04:01.008
Really? Who?

04:01.041 --> 04:02.610
Helen, her name was.

04:02.643 --> 04:05.779
There's no nurse
in maternity named Helen.

04:11.485 --> 04:13.787
It should be noted
 that moments before

04:13.821 --> 04:16.023
getting the call that
 would change everything,

04:16.055 --> 04:18.459
Michael was feeling...
 well, I'll be honest--

04:18.492 --> 04:20.793
a little blue.

04:20.827 --> 04:22.363
You okay, buddy?

04:22.396 --> 04:24.565
Oh, yeah.

04:24.598 --> 04:25.999
Just, uh, I don't know,

04:26.033 --> 04:28.402
a little blue.
(chuckles)

04:28.436 --> 04:29.970
Yeah. Me, too.

04:30.003 --> 04:32.039
I got passed over
for a promotion.

04:32.072 --> 04:33.607
Again.

04:33.641 --> 04:36.444
Ah, that sucks.

04:36.477 --> 04:38.912
My ex-fiancée was,
uh, accidentally

04:38.946 --> 04:40.781
artificially inseminated
with the sperm

04:40.814 --> 04:43.083
of this rich hotel owner,
who she just happened

04:43.116 --> 04:44.918
to have a crush on
in high school.

04:44.952 --> 04:47.421
And they had their
baby tonight, so...

04:48.689 --> 04:51.392
Wow. You win.

04:51.425 --> 04:53.761
(cell phone rings)

04:53.794 --> 04:55.329
Hello.

04:55.363 --> 04:56.997
ROSE:
Hello, Detective Cordero.

04:59.032 --> 05:00.100
Rose?

05:00.133 --> 05:03.036
Or Sin Rostro.

05:03.070 --> 05:06.006
(chuckles): I always did love
a good play on words.

05:06.039 --> 05:07.475
Why are you calling?

05:07.508 --> 05:09.510
Because I have
something you want.

05:09.543 --> 05:10.878
I want answers!
That's what I want!

05:10.911 --> 05:12.580
Where is our son?!
We don't know.

05:12.613 --> 05:14.515
The baby's
not in the hospital.

05:14.548 --> 05:16.049
And I've just got word
that surveillance tapes

05:16.083 --> 05:18.552
show the woman, the
one Jane described...

05:18.586 --> 05:20.454
According to his chart,
he hasn't had his hearing test.

05:20.488 --> 05:21.789
Oh, it was a full house earlier.
I'm sorry.

05:21.822 --> 05:23.591
No problem.
I'll take him.

05:23.624 --> 05:24.758
...she's on surveillance
leaving the building.

05:24.792 --> 05:26.427
We've called the police

05:26.460 --> 05:27.561
and we've issued
 an AMBER Alert.

05:27.595 --> 05:29.029
ROGELIO:
I'll retweet it.

05:29.062 --> 05:31.131
XIOMARA:
Jane, honey?

05:31.164 --> 05:32.566
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Which brings us here now,

05:32.600 --> 05:34.502
to that moment I mentioned,

05:34.535 --> 05:36.404
when Jane wished
 for a theme song.

05:36.437 --> 05:38.439
Something to tell her
 it would be all right.

05:38.472 --> 05:40.641
But there wasn't a theme song.

05:40.674 --> 05:42.075
There was only...

05:42.109 --> 05:44.712
(cell phone ringing)

05:47.180 --> 05:48.882
Michael?

05:48.916 --> 05:50.050
Hey.
Michael, someone took him.

05:50.083 --> 05:51.619
Someone took Mateo.

05:51.652 --> 05:52.986
Jane, I-I need you to listen
to me for a second.

05:53.020 --> 05:54.555
Are you listening?
What is happening?

05:54.588 --> 05:57.591
Jane, listen, I need you
to clear out the room.

05:57.625 --> 05:59.126
I know who has Mateo
and I know how to get him back.

05:59.159 --> 06:00.928
(gasping)

06:05.699 --> 06:06.734
Wait, Rose?

06:06.767 --> 06:08.702
I don't understand.

06:08.736 --> 06:09.970
What does she want?

06:10.003 --> 06:11.672
ROSE:
Let's call it a trade.

06:11.705 --> 06:13.407
I had a dragonfly broach.

06:16.076 --> 06:18.679
Luisa took it
 when we last saw each other.

06:18.712 --> 06:21.615
(moaning)

06:21.649 --> 06:23.817
And it was of real value.

06:23.851 --> 06:26.987
Apparently, it was logged into
evidence at your police station.

06:27.020 --> 06:30.190
Get it out
and I'll give you Mateo.

06:30.223 --> 06:31.592
RAFAEL:
Do the police even do that?

06:31.625 --> 06:33.160
Do they make trades?
It doesn't matter.

06:33.193 --> 06:35.696
This can't be official.
She said just me.

06:35.729 --> 06:36.997
What?!
Look,
following her instructions

06:37.030 --> 06:38.766
is the quickest,
safest way to get Mateo back.

06:38.799 --> 06:40.100
And that is all I want.

06:41.669 --> 06:42.936
You know that's all I want.

06:42.970 --> 06:45.639
I trust him, please.

06:47.040 --> 06:48.842
Fine, but I am going with you.

06:48.876 --> 06:50.444
Okay.
Me, too!

06:51.679 --> 06:52.713
Wait, what?

06:52.746 --> 06:53.747
No, you just gave birth.

06:53.781 --> 06:55.182
Yeah, exactly.

06:55.215 --> 06:56.717
I'm his mother.

06:56.750 --> 06:58.552
And I have to feed
him in 92 minutes.

06:58.586 --> 07:00.554
So I'm not gonna just
sit here and wait.

07:00.588 --> 07:02.823
I'm going. End of story.

07:02.856 --> 07:04.925
(theme song playing)

07:04.958 --> 07:07.695
I'm just gonna need
a hand out of bed.

07:07.728 --> 07:09.697
Grab those wipes.

07:09.730 --> 07:11.665
And-and grab that burp cloth.

07:11.699 --> 07:13.133
Oh, and I need pants.

07:14.668 --> 07:15.936
Hey, can you grab me
that bag of, um,

07:15.969 --> 07:18.639
adult diapers?

07:18.672 --> 07:20.708
All right, let's go!

07:20.741 --> 07:22.743
(groaning)

07:31.685 --> 07:33.521
81 minutes;
Mateo has to eat in 81 minutes.

07:33.554 --> 07:36.056
Just answer me--
did you take the pin?

07:36.089 --> 07:38.191
You don't have it?

07:38.225 --> 07:39.727
You're not gonna
get in trouble.

07:39.760 --> 07:41.228
Did you take the pin?

07:41.261 --> 07:42.663
We'll be right there.

07:42.696 --> 07:43.697
Wait,
where are we going?

07:43.731 --> 07:44.765
Who has it?
Your sister.

07:44.798 --> 07:45.966
Luisa?!
(gasps)

07:45.999 --> 07:47.701
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 No, not Luisa!

07:47.735 --> 07:50.170
RAFAEL:
Luisa, calm down.

07:54.875 --> 07:57.244
Ah, who am I kidding?

07:59.780 --> 08:01.615
Where is the pin?

08:01.649 --> 08:04.652
I w-went to get it

08:04.685 --> 08:06.687
and...

08:15.829 --> 08:18.265
What's that, babe?

08:23.804 --> 08:25.005
Oh, nothing.

08:25.038 --> 08:26.273
The police just wanted

08:26.306 --> 08:27.841
something to do with Rose.

08:27.875 --> 08:29.877
Your ex-girlfriend?

08:29.910 --> 08:31.745
Um, it's some, like,
evidence thing.

08:31.779 --> 08:34.715
You kept a box
of her stuff?

08:34.748 --> 08:36.650
No!

08:36.683 --> 08:37.851
Okay, yeah, but...

08:37.885 --> 08:39.620
They-they were
just cataloging so much,

08:39.653 --> 08:40.688
I didn't think
that they would miss it.

08:40.721 --> 08:41.722
You saved things from your

08:41.755 --> 08:42.956
psychopath ex-girlfriend?!

08:42.990 --> 08:44.725
Okay, first of all,
she's not a psychopath.

08:44.758 --> 08:46.794
She's a sociopath.
Oh, my God!

08:46.827 --> 08:49.129
You're still hung up on her!
No, Juicy, I swear, I'm not.

08:49.162 --> 08:50.631
I'm really not.

08:50.664 --> 08:51.799
Will you just please
give that back?

08:51.832 --> 08:53.100
No! No friggin' way!

08:53.133 --> 08:54.101
Juicy! Juicy!
No!

08:54.134 --> 08:55.268
Wait!

08:55.302 --> 08:57.137
No!

09:02.309 --> 09:03.343
Oh, no!

09:03.376 --> 09:04.945
(moaning)

09:04.978 --> 09:07.114
Oh!

09:08.215 --> 09:09.883
(Jane sighs)

09:09.917 --> 09:11.919
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Go. Go!

09:33.073 --> 09:34.775
(gasps)

09:34.808 --> 09:36.910
Guys, I got it!

09:36.944 --> 09:38.812
(grunts)
Come on!

09:38.846 --> 09:40.881
Hurry up and get
out of the pool!

09:40.914 --> 09:42.916
XIOMARA:
 She'll call.

09:42.950 --> 09:44.785
The minute Jane has
him, she'll call.

09:44.818 --> 09:46.086
(phone chimes)

09:46.119 --> 09:47.320
(gasps)

09:47.354 --> 09:49.790
(sighs)
Just Gloria Estefan.

09:49.823 --> 09:51.892
She wants to know
if there's anything she can do.

10:13.180 --> 10:14.815
Give me the baby.

10:14.848 --> 10:16.349
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Ah, yes.

10:16.383 --> 10:18.218
You remember Nadine, right?

10:25.826 --> 10:28.195
Do you at least understand now
why I went to work for her?

10:28.228 --> 10:30.964
This, this is
what she does, Michael.

10:30.998 --> 10:33.433
She makes it so
that you can't say no.
(baby fusses)

10:33.466 --> 10:35.302
Give me Mateo.

10:36.937 --> 10:38.305
Where's the pin?

10:40.774 --> 10:43.143
Do you even want to know
what's on the chip inside?

10:43.176 --> 10:44.978
No.

10:45.012 --> 10:47.147
All of the faces
Sin Rostro changed--

10:47.180 --> 10:48.849
crime bosses, drug lords.

10:48.882 --> 10:51.284
It's a record of what
they looked like before

10:51.318 --> 10:53.453
and what they look like now.

10:53.486 --> 10:56.323
Still want to trade?

10:56.356 --> 10:57.691
Yes.

10:57.725 --> 10:59.326
Huh.

10:59.359 --> 11:01.461
Rose was right.

11:01.494 --> 11:04.932
See, I wasn't so sure
you would do it.

11:08.401 --> 11:09.970
Oh, my God.

11:10.003 --> 11:12.372
Oh! Go! Run!

11:12.405 --> 11:15.008
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 And so, Rafael ran.

11:16.176 --> 11:18.145
(baby fussing)
 And then, even though

11:18.178 --> 11:19.479
she shouldn't have been
 physically able to,

11:19.512 --> 11:22.249
Jane ran, too.

11:22.282 --> 11:24.885
Well, we'll call it running,
 that thing she's doing.

11:24.918 --> 11:28.255
The point is Jane made it
 to her son.

11:28.288 --> 11:29.890
Oh, you're okay.

11:29.923 --> 11:32.125
You're okay. Mommy's here.

11:32.159 --> 11:35.128
Aww, and they all lived

11:35.162 --> 11:37.330
happily ever after.

11:37.364 --> 11:39.266
Well, except for Jane.

11:39.299 --> 11:42.269
And Rafael and Michael.

11:42.302 --> 11:44.271
And things are really
 screwed up with Luisa,

11:44.304 --> 11:47.407
and Xo and Ro, and don't
 get me started on Petra.

11:47.440 --> 11:50.077
Anyway, let's just enjoy
 this moment.

11:50.110 --> 11:52.813
Because it won't last.

11:52.846 --> 11:54.147
It's okay.

11:58.451 --> 11:59.920
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 And so,

11:59.953 --> 12:01.789
Mateo Gloriano Rogelio
 Solano Villanueva

12:01.822 --> 12:04.324
had quite a dramatic
 first night,

12:04.357 --> 12:06.960
causing enough worry
 for a lifetime.

12:06.994 --> 12:09.096
So he was gone
142 minutes...

12:09.129 --> 12:10.998
A fact his mother
 would remind him

12:11.031 --> 12:12.766
when, at 16,

12:12.800 --> 12:15.035
he was nearly two hours late
 for his curfew.

12:15.068 --> 12:17.537
...which is only 20 minutes
from when I would have fed him.

12:17.570 --> 12:19.773
But that's the distant future.

12:19.807 --> 12:22.943
Right now, Jane just wanted
 to hear two little words.

12:22.976 --> 12:24.244
He looks great.

12:24.277 --> 12:26.113
He's fine.
Oh!

12:26.146 --> 12:27.380
That's what I was thinking,

12:27.414 --> 12:28.916
but "He looks great"
 works, too.

12:28.949 --> 12:30.117
I'm sorry, I'm just so happy.

12:30.150 --> 12:31.885
DOCTOR:
So let's get him
on the scale, huh?

12:31.919 --> 12:32.953
Okay.

12:32.986 --> 12:34.454
(squeals)

12:34.487 --> 12:36.023
Okay, looks like

12:36.056 --> 12:37.557
he's six pounds and nine ounces.
Wait, what?

12:37.590 --> 12:39.259
He was seven pounds
when he was born.

12:39.292 --> 12:41.128
Why would he lose weight?
Well, it can
actually take babies

12:41.161 --> 12:43.063
up to two weeks to get back up
to their birth weight,

12:43.096 --> 12:45.098
which is why I'm not
too concerned.

12:45.132 --> 12:47.134
Oh, you can get him now.

12:49.436 --> 12:51.471
Okay, so you're not
 too concerned.

12:51.504 --> 12:53.440
Does that mean
that you're a little concerned?

12:53.473 --> 12:54.942
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Observe Jane

12:54.975 --> 12:56.143
trying not to panic.

12:56.176 --> 12:58.946
Well, that's about
ten percent already,

12:58.979 --> 13:00.848
so it's at the outer
limits of normal,

13:00.881 --> 13:02.315
but you're nursing.

13:02.349 --> 13:04.084
So it's likely your milk
just hasn't come in.

13:04.117 --> 13:05.152
Should we get him
a bottle, maybe?

13:05.185 --> 13:06.854
No, I really want nursing
to work.

13:06.887 --> 13:09.022
No, I just mean
in the meantime.

13:09.056 --> 13:10.023
Bottles can get
in the way.

13:10.057 --> 13:11.358
It's a supply
and demand thing.

13:11.391 --> 13:13.160
The more the baby eats,
the more she makes.

13:13.193 --> 13:16.129
Look who was paying attention
in lactation class.

13:16.163 --> 13:17.564
Oh, right,

13:17.597 --> 13:19.532
the one he was too busy
 to come to.

13:19.566 --> 13:21.168
There could also be
nipple confusion.

13:21.201 --> 13:23.170
Mom, now you're just
showing off.

13:23.203 --> 13:25.572
Observe Rafael
 trying to pretend he knows

13:25.605 --> 13:27.941
what nipple confusion is.

13:27.975 --> 13:29.009
It means that Mateo
can get confused

13:29.042 --> 13:30.577
between the bottle
and the breast

13:30.610 --> 13:33.146
and the concern is that
he would prefer the bottle.

13:33.180 --> 13:35.215
Just try to contribute
 something, man.

13:35.248 --> 13:37.150
Not if he's my son.

13:37.184 --> 13:40.187
Ooh, not that.

13:40.220 --> 13:41.088
So, how's the nursing
been going?

13:41.121 --> 13:42.322
I thought okay,

13:42.355 --> 13:43.490
just short.

13:43.523 --> 13:44.925
He falls asleep pretty quickly.

13:44.958 --> 13:46.026
Oh, you have to nip that
in the bud.

13:46.059 --> 13:48.028
